extends ./__post-layout.pug

block post-content
    p.post-container__text-block In an era of rapid technological progress, the integration of automation and artificial intelligence (AI) is reshaping care management. Care management involves the coordination and delivery of healthcare services to patients, a task that can be complex and cumbersome due to fragmented data, manual processes, and redundant workflows. However, as discussed in the article&nbsp;
        a(href='https://www.forbes.com/sites/forbestechcouncil/2023/10/16/modernizing-care-management-with-ai--automation/?sh=1a45a55d28e6' target='_blank') "Modernizing Care Management With AI & Automation,"&nbsp;
        | automation through AI has the potential to revolutionize the current state of care management.

    p.post-container__text-block 
        strong 1. Reducing Administrative & Repetitive Work
        br
        span Automation is pivotal in alleviating the administrative workload on healthcare professionals. By automating tasks such as appointment scheduling, patient registration, and insurance verification, valuable time is freed for providers to focus on delivering high-quality care. The potential savings from automating manual transactions, according to the Council for Affordable Quality Healthcare, could reach $13.3 billion annually, with significant contributions from intake, reconciliation, and insurance verification.

    p.post-container__text-block
        strong 2. Promoting Preventative Care
        br
        span AI-driven analytics can swiftly process vast amounts of healthcare data, providing insights that aid care management decisions. This includes predicting social risks, readmission risks, and disease progression, then tailoring treatment plans based on data-driven evidence. This approach allows for more accurate patient risk assessment, ultimately reducing long-term healthcare costs by offering preventive services or interventions.

    p.post-container__text-block
        strong 3. Improving Communication & Coordination
        br
        span Communication failures are a leading cause of medical errors, but AI-powered platforms facilitate seamless communication and data sharing among care team members, patients, and family members. It reduces errors and improves patients’ understanding of care. Automation and AI also enable continuous remote monitoring of patients with chronic conditions through wearable devices and sensors, allowing timely intervention to prevent avoidable utilization.

    p.post-container__text-block
        strong 4. Increasing Engagement and Adherence
        br
        span AI-powered chatbots and virtual assistants assist patient engagement by providing personalized health education and guidance. Integrating automated outreach and patient education into a holistic strategy can improve adherence to treatment plans, leading to greater health outcomes and lower costs.


    p.post-container__text-block
        strong 4. Conclusion
        br
        span The integration of AI and automation is propelling a new era of care management for healthcare providers. This evolution promotes modernized care coordination while considering cost, quality, equity, and experience. As these technologies become more deeply integrated into digital healthcare ecosystems, the potential to transform care management is immense, leading to better patient outcomes and a more efficient healthcare system overall.

    p.post-container__text-block
